.TH add_decomp_filler  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBadd_decomp_filler\fR \-  Inserts breaker cells to divide the chip into several small parts
.SH Syntax \fBadd_decomp_filler\fR   [-help]   -bottom_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}   -core_column_cell {<cell_name>}  -core_row_cell {<cell_name_list>}   [-offsetx <offset_in_microns>]  [-offsety <offset_in_microns>]  [-power_domain <power_domain_name>]  [-prefix <prefix_name>]  -stepx <step_in_microns>   -stepy <step_in_microns>  -top_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}   -vertical_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}
.P Inserts breaker cells to divide the chip into several small parts. This reduces the run time of coloring while manufacturing the chip.
.P This command is run after floorPlan and before addEndCap. 
.SH Parameters    "\fB-bottom_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}\fR" Specifies the CA-break end cap cell for rows, to make bottom_edge of endcap face core.  "\fB-core_column_cell {<cell_name>}\fR" Specifies the CA-break filler cell for inserting into columns.   "\fB-core_row_cell {<cell_name_list>}\fR" Specifies a list of CA-break filler cells inserted horizontally in the core rows.   "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes type and default information for each add_decomp_filler parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command: man add_decomp_filler.  "\fB-offsetx <offset_in_microns>\fR" Specifies the offset added to the first step in the horizontal direction.  "\fB-offsety <offset_in_microns>\fR" Specifies the offset added to the first step in the vertical direction.   "\fB-power_domain <power_domain_name>\fR" Specifies the power domain for which CA-break filler cells are to be inserted.  Note: If the -power_domain option is used, the offset value is applied to the specified power domain. However, if the -power domain is not specified, the offset value is applied to all available power domains. To use different offset value for a specific power domain, you first need to delete the CA fillers from the power domain if it is already filled and then reinsert CA filler to the power domain with the target offset value.  "\fB-prefix <prefix_name>\fR" Specifies the prefix for decomp cells. If this option is specified, the user-specified prefix is applied to all inserted decomp fillers, else the default prefix name is used.   "\fB-stepx <step_in_microns>\fR" Specifies the decomposition step in horizontal direction.   "\fB-stepy <step_in_microns>\fR" Specifies the decomposition step in vertical direction.   "\fB-top_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}\fR" Specifies CA-break end cap cell for rows, to make top_edge of endcap face core.   "\fB-vertical_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}\fR" Specifies CA-break end cap cell inserted at the left and right edges as end caps. 
.SH Example
.P The code below shows the usage of the add_decomp_filler command. 
.P add_decomp_filler
.P -core_row_cell {CA_ROW2 CA_ROW3} -core_column_cell {CA_COL2}
.P -top_edge_endcap CA_TE -bottom_edge_endcap CA_BE
.P -vertical_edge_endcap CA_LRE
.P -stepx 500 -stepy 500
